As of the census of 2000, there were 299 people, 108 households, and 80 families residing in the town. The population density was 453.3 people per square mile (174.9/km²). There were 112 housing units at an average density of 169.8 per square mile (65.5/km²). The racial makeup of the town was 95.65% White, 0.33% African American, 1.67% Native American, 0.33% Asian, and 2.01% from two or more races, also known as mulattoes.
